Family Dynamics & Screen Time Survey Dataset

Collection Method

The dataset used in this project was created through a self-designed online survey titled "Family Dynamics & Screen Time Survey." Rather than using an existing dataset from public repositories such as Kaggle, UCI Machine Learning Repository, or other online sources, the data was collected personally using Google Forms and stored automatically in Google Sheets. The purpose of the survey was to examine how different household characteristics relate to the amount of time families spend using digital screens for leisure and entertainment.

The questionnaire was distributed to family members, friends, classmates, and members of the local community through online messaging platforms. Each participant completed the questionnaire only once, providing information about their household composition, the number of children living in the home, the number of smartphones regularly used, the primary employment style of the household's main income earners, gaming console ownership, and the total number of leisure screen hours during a typical weekday.

Collecting the dataset personally ensured that it represented real responses from participants instead of relying on pre-existing public datasets. Since respondents entered their own answers, the dataset naturally contains inconsistencies, formatting differences, and a few unusual values. These imperfections make the dataset realistic and suitable for demonstrating data cleaning and preprocessing techniques in later stages of the Data Science lifecycle.

