## Description of Features and Label

The dataset contains several independent variables (features) that describe household characteristics, together with one dependent variable (label) that represents the total amount of screen time.

### Features (X)

1. Household Size

This feature records the total number of people living full-time in the household, including the respondent.

2. Number of Household Members Under 18

This numerical feature represents how many members of the household are younger than eighteen years old.

3. Number of Smartphones

This feature records the number of smartphones that are regularly used by members of the household.

4. Primary Income Source or Working Style

This categorical feature describes the main working arrangement or income source of the household. Responses include Office Work, Remote Work, Shift Work, Student, Retired, Business, Daily Work, and several manually entered responses.

5. Gaming Console Ownership

This categorical feature records whether the household owns a gaming console such as a PlayStation, Xbox, or Nintendo Switch. The responses are "Yes" or "No."

### Label (Y)

Combined Leisure Screen Time (Hours)

The target variable is the combined number of hours that all household members spend using digital screens for entertainment during a typical weekday. This value is numerical and represents the outcome that could be predicted using the household characteristics.

